   MONSANTO-NORRIS-COLUMN (Undated) _ Seldom in human history has a
technology with such exciting possibilities seemed less popular
than genetic modification of foods is today. The way things are
going, executives at Monsanto, the leading company in the field,
might have to start lying about what they do. Perhaps they'd be
better off if they claimed to be from Philip Morris. By Floyd
Norris.
</P>
