illustrations, passages from a couple of the books. (Bookman,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution freelancer; not for use by NYTNS
clients). 40.
</P>
<P>
   WARNER-ON-WOOD - ATLANTA - ''Joinery Shaping &AMP; Milling,''
another new book from The Taunton Press, is one that deserves a
place in every student woodworker's library alongside the same
publisher's classic ''Tage Frid Teaches Woodworking'' series.
(Warner, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   RELIGION
</P>
<P>
   RELIGION-ENDTIME - For 2,000 years Christians have been
expecting Jesus to return and the world as we know it to end. But
several hundred years before that, the Book of Daniel addressed the
end of the world. We look at prophecies over the years that have
been made - and not come to pass, religious movements that were
based on those predictions, and the modern theological arguments
over when, and how, the world will end. With timeline, glossary of
end-time terms, box detailing beliefs of other religions and list
of books, movies, etc. dealing with end-time themes. (White,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 50. WITH ILLUSTRATION and LAYOUTS.
</P>
<P>
   NEW-FAITH - AUSTIN, Texas - From fundamentalist to mainline
Christians, the words ''religion'' and ''religious,'' which many
believe synonymous with a church institution, are being cast aside
in favor of personalized spirituality. It's a dramatic shift, one
of the biggest of the millennium, according to some theologians and
scholars. What has evolved, mostly in recent decades, is a new
perspective on how faith can be practiced, leading to declining
membership in mainline denominations, religion-hopping and a
freestyle approach to faith that shows no signs of letting up.
(Perkes, Austin American-Statesman) MOVED MONDAY.
</P>
