 (Repeating as part of a weekly roundup of computer features)  
Law resources on the Net 
By Omar L. Gallaga  
c.1999 Cox News Service  
<TEXT>
<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas _ We swear to show you legal sites, a whole bunch
of legal sites and nothing but the legal sites in this week's
e-traveler. See what we've found in this list of law and
lawyer-related sites:
</P>
<P>
   www.law.com _ A clearinghouse of information about the legal
world for law professionals and the people who love them. (You
don't love lawyers? So sue us.) Law.com includes legal news,
information for law students, resources and an interesting service
where you can get a free e-mail address with the (at)law.com
domain. Want to scare someone with the threat of legal action? Send
it to them from that e-mail address.
</P>
<P>
   www.nolo.com _ Just like doctors at parties, lawyers hate to be
bugged for free advice. So Nolo, the publisher of many self-help
legal books, has a Web site designed ``for the little guy.'' You
can ask Auntie Nolo for common-sense answers to legal questions or
browse frequently asked questions about more than 500 legal
dilemmas. wwlia.org/hist.htm _ If you want to bone up on your legal
history, the World Wide Legal Information Association has compiled
a list dating from 2350 B.C.'s Urukagina's Code to the 1948 General
Agreement on Tariffs and Trade. Think of it as Cliffs Notes for the
history of law.
</P>
<P>
   www.stanford.edu/group/WLHP _Before there were ``L.A. Law's''
Grace Van Owen and Ally McBeal on TV, there were Betty Reynolds
Cobb and Dorothy Kenyon, pioneering women in the field of law.
Stanford Law School's Women's Legal History Biography Project lists
female lawyers through history and includes biographies, research
leads and articles. Inspiring.
</P>
<P>
   www.personal.usyd. edu.au/(tilde)atan/jokes/canonicallawyer.html
_ And of course, where would we be without jokes about lawyers? The
Canonical List of Lawyer Humor includes riddles, courtroom humor
and all manner of jibes on the legal front. If you're ever in need
of a good lawyer joke, this is the place to go.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
NYT-12-13-99 1110EST &QL;
</P>
