 (Repeating as part of a weekly roundup of computer features)  
Our cup warmeth over 
c.1999 Cox News Service  
<TEXT>
<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas _ When making that grand list of annoying gadgets,
you have to include the cup warmer. Who thought of this ingenious
device? If you're not familiar with the cup warmer, it could best
be described as a disc that heats up and, in theory, keeps your cup
warm. Believe me, this is only in theory. This death disc does
nothing except heat the bottom of your cup to such an intense heat
that its only practical use is ritualistic burning of the flesh
(or, if you're on the creative side of things, you can use it to
fuse glass beads and make pretty sculptures). This gadget actually
has the ability to transcend ``annoying'' and enter the hallowed
realm of ``hyper-annoying.'' To attain this, all you have to do is
plug in the cup warmer next to a colleague's computer, let it heat
up and don't put a cup on it. The howls and screams will tell it
all.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
