<P>
   FBC-RHODEN-COLUMN (Undated) _ Sports of The Times column on
Notre Dame: Yes, the most famous football school in the country got
nailed for the first time, but in these days of constant
transgressions at the college level, it somehow doesn't seem either
surprising or offensive. By William C. Rhoden.
</P>
<P>
   FBC-NOTRE-DAME (Undated) _ The most storied college football
program in the country received NCAA penalties for the first time
in its history, as the University of Notre Dame lost two
scholarships stemming from a two-year investigation into a
booster's gifts to players. By Frank Litsky.
</P>
