</P>
<P>
   MOVIE-ANNA (Undated) _ ``Anna and the King'' is a lot more than
``The King and I'' minus Rodgers' and Hammerstein's music. It's a
broader, wider, deeper, fuller canvas. By Jay Carr. 875 words.
</P>
<P>
   MOVIE-BICENTENNIAL (Undated) _ ``Bicentennial Man'' is the kind
of movie that makes you wish Robin Williams would say enough with
the touchy-feely stuff already. By Jay Carr.
</P>
<P>
   MOVIE-STUART (Undated) _ The impetus to see ``Stuart Little''
will come largely from parents who fondly remember the E. B. White
classic about the mouse who refuses to think small. By Jay Carr.
530 words.
</P>
<P>
   MOVIE-CIDER (Undated) _ ``The Cider House Rules'' is the best
film to date of a John Irving novel. The author, who does not
lightly bestow his imprimatur, would have only himself to blame if
it weren't. By Jay Carr. 940 words.
</P>
<P>
   MUSIC-BOX (Undated) _ Sony, Stevie, and Sammy top this year's
sets. By Steve Morse. 1200 words.
</P>
<P>
   w/
</P>
<P>
   MUSIC-DEAD (Undated) _ ``So Many Roads (1965-1995),'' a new
five-CD boxed set, comes closer to capturing the Grateful Dead than
any of the ``greatest'' Dead collections like ``What a Long Strange
Trip It's Been.'' By Matthew Gilbert. 950 words.
</P>
<P>
   MUSIC-ROCK (Undated) _ The J. Geils Band will play a benefit for
the families of the dead Worcester firefighters Dec. 29 at the
Orpheum in Boston. By Steve Morse.
</P>
