<P>
   FANTASIA-2000 (LOS ANGELES) -- The Walt Disney Co. will release
``Fantasia 2000'' on 35mm after its initial run on large-format
Imax, the company's distribution chief acknowledged. Disney had
been hush-hush about whether it would release the updated animation
classic at conventional theaters, but its holiday card -- sent to
thousands of friends, associates and vendors of the company --
inadvertently spilled the beans. On the back of the card is a
highlights list of the coming year, including the nationwide
release of ``Fantasia 2000.'' By Dave McNary (Will move on the
``f'' financial and ``e'' entertainment news wires.)
