<P>
   DREYERS-FLAVOR (LOS ANGELES) -- I scream. You scream. We all
scream for Gold Miner's Dream ice cream. After a three-month
taste-off, the frozen creation of 11-year-old Elysa Hill of
Woodland Hills in suburban Los Angeles has been named the official
flavor of the California Sesquicentennial. Hill's ice cream will be
in stores from Eureka to San Diego in Dreyer's famous half-gallon
size beginning in mid-January, said Howard. But hurry out to get
it: Gold Miner's Dream will only be available to the public next
year. By Chris Sieroty (Will move on the ``f'' financial news
wire.)
</P>
