<P>
   SAILORS-VIEQUES (Aboard the USS Dwight D. Eisenhower) _ The
bitter eight-month stalemate over the future Navy use of a disputed
target range on the Puerto Rican island of Vieques falls heavily on
some sailors on this aircraft carrier. They are Puerto Ricans who
voice loyalties to both the Navy and to the commonwealth's crusade
to oust the Navy from Vieques after 58 years. By STEWART M. POWELL.
(Filed Friday.)
</P>
