<P>
   Y2K-CZAR (Washington) _ People watching television news on New
Year's weekend will likely see a lot of John Koskinen, the White
House's Y2K czar. But Koskinen hopes that once the weekend is over,
few Americans will remember his name. To him that would mean the
United States experienced relatively few Y2K-related problems. By
JENNIFER CORBETT DOOREN. (Filed Thursday).
</P>
