Republicans what Franklin D. Roosevelt has been to Democrats for
many decades _ an icon to be praised, worshipped and copied. That
would please Reagan because he greatly admired FDR and sought in
many ways to emulate him. By ROBERT E. THOMPSON. (Filed Wednesday)
