   TOP
</P>
<P>
   Lead story:
</P>
<P>
   IRAQ-U.N. (United Nations) _ A divided Security Council votes to
create a new arms inspection system for Iraq with the promise to
President Saddam Hussein that sanctions against his country could
be suspended within a year and eventually lifted if he cooperates.
By Barbara Crossette. (We plan to move the story by 8 p.m. ET in
``i'' news file.) 1,700 words.
</P>
<P>
   Top center:
</P>
<P>
   EPA-AIR-POLLUTION (Washington) _ The Environmental Protection
Agency orders 392 plants, mostly electric generating stations, in a
dozen states, to cut in half emissions of chemicals that drift with
prevailing winds and add to smog along the Eastern seaboard. The
regulators acted at the request of New York, Connecticut,
Massachusetts and Pennsylvania, which said they needed help to meet
national smog standards. By Matthew L. Wald. (Scheduled to move by
9 p.m. ET in ``w'' news file.)
</P>
