   With map.
</P>
<P>
   2-column photo reefer to inside wire story on the space shuttle
Discovery.
</P>
<P>
   Off-lead story:
</P>
<P>
   MEXICO-SUBURBS (Mexico City) _ A new class of commuters has
emerged in Mexico. A half-century after Americans began to abandon
cities for suburbs, thousands of Mexicans are for the first time
making a similar choice, fleeing the pollution and clamor of Mexico
City in search of quiet homes, well-clipped lawns and safer streets
in cities and towns hours away from the capital. By Sam Dillon.
(The story has moved in ``i'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   With map.
</P>
<P>
   FOLD
</P>
<P>
   NY-TOBACCO-TAX (Albany, N.Y.) _ Gov. George Pataki and
legislative leaders from both major parties agree to raise the
state's cigarette tax by 55 cents a pack in an ambitious effort to
provide health care coverage for as many as one million uninsured
New Yorkers. By Raymond Hernandez. (Scheduled to move by 9 p.m. ET
in ``a'' news file.) 1,600 words.
</P>
