<P>
   CANADA-FARMS (Sperling, Manitoba) _ As recently as the 1950s,
this farming village outside Winnipeg supported a restaurant, two
churches, three stores and a high school. But free-market policies
_ slashing farm subsidies, allowing inefficient farmers to fail and
promoting productive techniques for the survivors _ have radically
transformed the human landscape here. Since 1970, Sperling's
population has dropped by half. By James Brooke.
</P>
