<P>
   The Seattle Post-Intelligencer plans to move the following
stories for clients of the NYTimes News Service for editions of
Saturday, December 18, and thereafter. If you have any questions,
please call Bob Schenet on the national-foreign desk at (206)
448-8037.
</P>
<P>
   ARMY-WHISTLEBLOWER (Fort Lewis, Wash.) _ When Army Dr. Stephen
Whitlock Smith took over the emergency room at the Landstuhl
Regional Medical Center in Germany six years ago, he found a
facility in deep crisis. But after pleading for help, and then
filing formal complaints, the situation changed into his own
personal crisis.
</P>
<P>
   By Ed Offley. (Story has moved in the ``a'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   BOMB-PLOT (Seattle) ) _ At least four federal agencies are
focusing on what seems likely to be a major bombing plot employing
powerful explosives that authorities stumbled upon in the little
logging and fishing town of Port Angeles, Wash.
</P>
<P>
   By Scott Sunde. (Story will move in the ``a'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   with BOMB-PLOT-POWER (Seattle) _ The explosive powder and liquid
seized in a rental car in Port Angeles are powerful enough to
destroy a mid-sized office building, according to a military
explosives expert.
</P>
<P>
   By Ed Offley. (Story will move in the ``a'' category.)
